{"title_page": "The Sunpilots", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = The Sunpilots\n| image           = Sunpilots.JPG\n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = Four men are performing in front of an audience. The man at left is playing a guitar with electrical switches and power boards in front of him. The next man has a microphone held in both hands at his mouth. The third man is seated behind a drum kit but has his arms akimbo on his knees and is looking to his left without touching his kit. The fourth man is playing a bass guitar, he is looking down at his strings. Immediately behind the band are bike racks. Further behind is fencing and at the left a bridge. On the bridge are people walking away, across the way are city buildings about five or six storeys tall.\n| caption         = Busking in Berlin, June 2014\n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = Sydney, New South Wales, Australia\n| genre           = [[Alternative rock]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|2006}}\u2013present\n| label           = Honeytrap\n| associated_acts = \n| website         = {{URL|thesunpilots.com/}}\n| current_members = \n* Raj Siva-Rajah\n* Bob Spencer\n* Kay Ketting\n* Stefan Bielik\n| past_members    = \n* Justin Kool\n* Andrew Nielsen\n* Tom McGirr\n* Adil Baktir\n}}\n\n'''The Sunpilots''' are a four-piece Australian-German [[alternative rock]] band formed in 2006 by mainstays Raj Siva-Rajah on lead vocals and Bob Spencer on lead guitar. They relocated to [[Berlin]] in September 2010. The group has issued two studio albums, ''Living Receiver'' (2009) and ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' (2012).\n\n==Formation and early days==\n\nThe Sunpilots were formed in Sydney in early 2006 by Raj Siva-Rajah on lead vocals and Bob Spencer on lead guitar. Siva-Rajah, from Brisbane, learnt [[Carnatic music]] from the age of eight.<ref name=\"Busby\"/> His family moved to Adelaide where he fronted local alternative rock bands in high school and college,<ref name=\"Busby\"/> he moved to Sydney, where he met Spencer. The early line-up of the Sunpilots included Gavin Collison on bass guitar and Anthony Soole on percussion.<ref name=\"Soul Bio\">{{cite web | url = http://www.soulshine.com.au/artist/The_Sunpilots.html | title = The Sunpilots | work = Soulshine: Australian Independent Music | accessdate = 28 October 2017 | url-status = bot: unknown | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/122966/20101115-1450/www.soulshine.com.au/artist/The_Sunpilots.html | archivedate = 15 November 2010 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots released a five-track extended play in June 2006 as their first release via Honeytrap Records. Tracks received national airplay on [[Triple J]] and [[Nova (radio network)|Nova]], winning the Producers Award at the Musicoz Awards later that year.<ref name=\"Busby\">{{cite web | url = http://fasterlouder.junkee.com/take-to-the-sky-with-the-sunpilots/777850 | title = Take to the Sky with the Sunpilots | last = Busby | first = Cec | date = 28 June 2006 | work = FasterLouder | publisher = [[Junkee Media]] | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> Siva-Rajah explained their preparations, \"every rehearsal it ends up coming out slightly different. We did that and it just ended up sounding OK and we thought we'd put it onto a CD and get it out there mainly because we thought, 'not a huge amount is going to happen out of the first release for a band'.\"<ref name=\"Busby\"/>\n\n==''Living Receiver'' (2007\u201309)==\n\nThe Sunpilots' began working on their debut album, ''Living Receiver'', in 2007 and enlisted the help of Australian producer [[Phil McKellar]] ([[Silverchair]], [[Powderfinger]], [[Grinspoon]]) as co-producer and mix engineer. The band embarked on their Cold Hands, Warm Heart tour in August 2007,  spanning five states, it was the band's first national tour.<ref name=\"Wilson\">{{cite news | url = https://issuu.com/dkqw/docs/sauce49 | title = Rock Salt: Argh! Aliens! Run! Run for Your Lives! | last = Wilson | first = Tom | issue = 49 | date = 22 August 2007 | work = Sauce | page = 4 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> A new version of \"Spotlight in the Sun\" was released in May as its first single with an associated music video.<ref name=\"Wilson\"/><ref name=\"MacLeod\">{{cite web | url = http://theinspirationroom.com/daily/2007/the-sunpilots-debut-spotlight-in-the-sun/ | title = The Sunpilots Debut 'Spotlight in the Sun' | work = The Inspiration Room | last = MacLeod | first = Duncan | date = 13 May 2007 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> It became the most added song on Australian radio during the week of 14 February 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radioinfo.com.au/news/radio-airplay-still-way-make-hit|title=Radio airplay still the way to make a hit {{!}} radioinfo.com.au|website=www.radioinfo.com.au|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> and the video aired nationally on pop music TV shows MTV, ''Rage'', Channel V and ''Video Hits''. The track was chosen as an iTunes Single of the Week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sunshinecoastdaily.com.au/news/sunpilots-set-course-coast/340187/|title=Sunpilots set course for Coast|work=Sunshine Coast Daily|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots finished recording ''Living Receiver'' in early 2008 and released it through their own label, Honeytrap Records, in August,<ref name=\"NLA Living\">{{Citation | author1 = Sunpilots | title = Living Receiver | publication-date = 2010 | publisher = Honeytrap Records | url = http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/188154942 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> followed by a national tour. The line-up was Siva-Rajah, Spencer, Justin Kool on bass guitar and Andy Nielsen on drums.<ref name=\"NLA Living\"/> The record won Best International Artist for the group at the Toronto Independent Music Awards<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| coauthors =| title =Toronto Independent Music Awards Winners| page =| publisher =| date =| url =http://torontoima.com/new/awards/| accessdate =20 April 2011}}</ref> and a Single of the Year at the LA Music Awards.<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| coauthors =| title =LA Music Awards| page =| publisher =| date =| url =http://www.lamusicawards.com| accessdate =}}</ref> The band was one of 15 rock music finalists in the International Songwriting Competition (nominated alongside fellow Australians, [[Eskimo Joe]]).<ref>{{cite news| title =ISC Winners 08| url =http://www.songwritingcompetition.com/winners.htm| url-status =dead| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20100807225624/http://www.songwritingcompetition.com/Winners.htm| archivedate =7 August 2010| df =dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 the Sunpilots toured Australia twice more for their March of the Drones and Animals in My Mind tours. During the second tour the band performed at the One Movement Festival in Perth with the Hilltop Hoods, Sarah Blasko, Little Red and Kate Miller-Heidke<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| title =One Movement for Music Announce Winners| page =| publisher =| date =16 October 2009| url =http://www.hotsource.com.au/news/1232/One_Movement_For_Music_Announce_Winners| accessdate =}}</ref> and were MySpace Featured Artists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soundsaustralia.com.au/downloads/midem2011_soundsaustralia.pdf|title=Sounds Australia \u2013 MIDEM 2011 booklet|website=Sounds Australia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409231246/http://www.soundsaustralia.com.au/downloads/MIDEM2011_SoundsAustralia.pdf|archive-date=2013-04-09|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' and move to Berlin (2010\u201315) ==\n\nIn 2010 the Sunpilots began working on their second album, ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues''. Following the completion of tracking at [[Studios 301]] in September, the band relocated to Berlin to tour Europe extensively.<ref>{{Citation|last=The Sunpilots|title=We Are The Sunpilots (Ep 1): Australian Nomads|date=2012-04-07|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNSkyTWJRkE|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref> They performed their first European show at the Popkomm Festival at Berlin Music Week 2010 on 9 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.messe-berlin.de/vip8_1/website/Internet/Internet/www.popkomm/deutsch/Popkomm-Showcase-Festival/Line-Up/index.jsp|title=Popkomm Showcase Festival blog|last=|first=|publisher=Popkomm|accessdate=}}</ref> ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' was mixed in Berlin by German engineer [[:de:Peter Schmidt (Tonmeister)|Peter Schmidt]] in late 2011 and released worldwide in 2012. The record is a dystopian [[concept album]] about \"human need for security and the freedoms we are willing to trade in return\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rockfreaks.net/albums/5139|title=The Sunpilots \u2013 ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' \u2013 Album Review | first = Petteri | last = Pertola | work = Rockfreaks.net | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots toured Europe from 2011 to 2015, performing over 400 shows at festivals and clubs in the UK, Germany, Austria, Switzerland, France, Sweden, Netherlands, Belgium, Italy, Poland, Slovenia, Lithuania and Latvia. In September 2014 they completed their first US tour, performing 65 shows across 35 states.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thesunpilots.com/tourdates|title=The Sunpilots - Tour Dates (past shows)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110316014322/http://www.thesunpilots.com/tourdates|archive-date=2011-03-16|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nDuring this time the band also became known for staying with their fans on tour<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.muzikdizcovery.com/2013/03/album-review-sunpilots-king-of.html|title=Album Review: The Sunpilots - King of the Sugarcoated Tongues|website=www.muzikdizcovery.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> and performing in [[Mauerpark]] near the Berlin Wall.<ref>{{Citation|last=Thorsten Neuhetzki|title=Sunpilots im Mauerpark Berlin|date=2016-07-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xn8_lsh-QQI|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref>\n\n== Upcoming record (2016 - present) ==\n\nThe Sunpilots began work on their third album in early 2016 and have launched a crowdfunding campaign to fund it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pledge.thesunpilots.com|title=Pledge {{!}} The Sunpilots|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417194749/http://pledge.thesunpilots.com|archive-date=2016-04-17|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album, which is being recorded in Spain and Berlin, is slated for release in late 2017 and will be followed by an extensive world tour.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pledge.thesunpilots.com/new-album-and-world-tour/progress-and-release-date|title=New album progress and release date|work=Pledge {{!}} The Sunpilots|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-AU}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016 the band took a break from recording to tour Canada.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thesunpilots.com/news/our-first-canada-tour-kicks-off-this-week|title=Our first Canada tour kicks off this week|work=The Sunpilots|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-AU}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n\n=== Current line-up ===\n\n* Raj Siva-Rajah (2006\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n* Bob Spencer (2006\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 guitar\n* Kay Ketting (2013\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Stefan Bielik (2015\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n\n=== Previous members ===\n\n* Gavin Collison (2006)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n* Anthony Soole (2006\u201307)&nbsp;\u2013 percussion<ref name=\"MacLeod\"/>\n* Rob Ewan (2007)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar<ref name=\"Wilson\"/>\n* Justin Kool (2009\u201312)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n* Andrew Nielsen (2009\u201311)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Tom McGirr (2011\u201312)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Adil Baktir (2012\u201315)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n\n* ''Living Receiver'' (2009)\n* ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' (2012)\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n\n* ''The Sunpilots'' (self-titled 5-track EP) (2006)\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n* ''Spotlight in the Sun'' (2007)\n* ''You're Gonna Be a Star'' (2008)\n* ''Drones'' (2009)\n* ''Animals in My Mind'' (2009)\n* ''The Piper's Mirror'' (2012)\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{Official website|thesunpilots.com}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sunpilots, The}}\n[[Category:New South Wales musical groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2006]]\n[[Category:Australian post-grunge groups]]\n[[Category:Australian indie rock groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = The Sunpilots\n| image           = Sunpilots.JPG\n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = Four men are performing in front of an audience. The man at left is playing a guitar with electrical switches and power boards in front of him. The next man has a microphone held in both hands at his mouth. The third man is seated behind a drum kit but has his arms akimbo on his knees and is looking to his left without touching his kit. The fourth man is playing a bass guitar, he is looking down at his strings. Immediately behind the band are bike racks. Further behind is fencing and at the left a bridge. On the bridge are people walking away, across the way are city buildings about five or six storeys tall.\n| caption         = Busking in Berlin, June 2014\n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = Sydney, New South Wales, Australia\n| genre           = [[Alternative rock]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|2006}}\u2013present\n| label           = Honeytrap\n| associated_acts = \n| website         = {{URL|thesunpilots.com/}}\n| current_members = \n* Raj Siva-Rajah\n* Bob Spencer\n* Kay Ketting\n* Stefan Bielik\n| past_members    = \n* Justin Kool\n* Andrew Nielsen\n* Tom McGirr\n* Adil Baktir\n}}\n\n'''The Sunpilots''' are a four-piece Australian-German [[alternative rock]] band formed in 2006 by mainstays Raj Siva-Rajah on lead vocals and Bob Spencer on lead guitar. They relocated to [[Berlin]] in September 2010. The group has issued two studio albums, ''Living Receiver'' (2009) and ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' (2012).\n\n==Formation and early days==\n\nThe Sunpilots were formed in Sydney in early 2006 by Raj Siva-Rajah on lead vocals and Bob Spencer on lead guitar. Siva-Rajah, from Brisbane, learnt [[Carnatic music]] from the age of eight.<ref name=\"Busby\"/> His family moved to Adelaide where he fronted local alternative rock bands in high school and college,<ref name=\"Busby\"/> he moved to Sydney where he met Spencer. The early line-up of the Sunpilots included Gavin Collison on bass guitar and Anthony Soole on percussion.<ref name=\"Soul Bio\">{{cite web | url = http://www.soulshine.com.au/artist/The_Sunpilots.html | title = The Sunpilots | work = Soulshine: Australian Independent Music | accessdate = 28 October 2017 | url-status = bot: unknown | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/122966/20101115-1450/www.soulshine.com.au/artist/The_Sunpilots.html | archivedate = 15 November 2010 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots released a five-track extended play in June 2006 as their first release via Honeytrap Records. Tracks received national airplay on [[Triple J]] and [[Nova (radio network)|Nova]], winning the Producers Award at the Musicoz Awards later that year.<ref name=\"Busby\">{{cite web | url = http://fasterlouder.junkee.com/take-to-the-sky-with-the-sunpilots/777850 | title = Take to the Sky with the Sunpilots | last = Busby | first = Cec | date = 28 June 2006 | work = FasterLouder | publisher = [[Junkee Media]] | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> Siva-Rajah explained their preparations, \"every rehearsal it ends up coming out slightly different. We did that and it just ended up sounding OK and we thought we'd put it onto a CD and get it out there mainly because we thought, 'not a huge amount is going to happen out of the first release for a band'.\"<ref name=\"Busby\"/>\n\n==''Living Receiver'' (2007\u201309)==\n\nThe Sunpilots' began working on their debut album, ''Living Receiver'', in 2007 and enlisted the help of Australian producer [[Phil McKellar]] ([[Silverchair]], [[Powderfinger]], [[Grinspoon]]) as co-producer and mix engineer. The band embarked on their Cold Hands, Warm Heart tour in August 2007,  spanning five states, it was the band's first national tour.<ref name=\"Wilson\">{{cite news | url = https://issuu.com/dkqw/docs/sauce49 | title = Rock Salt: Argh! Aliens! Run! Run for Your Lives! | last = Wilson | first = Tom | issue = 49 | date = 22 August 2007 | work = Sauce | page = 4 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> A new version of \"Spotlight in the Sun\" was released in May as its first single with an associated music video.<ref name=\"Wilson\"/><ref name=\"MacLeod\">{{cite web | url = http://theinspirationroom.com/daily/2007/the-sunpilots-debut-spotlight-in-the-sun/ | title = The Sunpilots Debut 'Spotlight in the Sun' | work = The Inspiration Room | last = MacLeod | first = Duncan | date = 13 May 2007 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> It became the most added song on Australian radio during the week of 14 February 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radioinfo.com.au/news/radio-airplay-still-way-make-hit|title=Radio airplay still the way to make a hit {{!}} radioinfo.com.au|website=www.radioinfo.com.au|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> and the video aired nationally on pop music TV shows MTV, ''Rage'', Channel V and ''Video Hits''. The track was chosen as an iTunes Single of the Week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sunshinecoastdaily.com.au/news/sunpilots-set-course-coast/340187/|title=Sunpilots set course for Coast|work=Sunshine Coast Daily|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots finished recording ''Living Receiver'' in early 2008 and released it through their own label, Honeytrap Records, in August,<ref name=\"NLA Living\">{{Citation | author1 = Sunpilots | title = Living Receiver | publication-date = 2010 | publisher = Honeytrap Records | url = http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/188154942 | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref> followed by a national tour. The line-up was Siva-Rajah, Spencer, Justin Kool on bass guitar and Andy Nielsen on drums.<ref name=\"NLA Living\"/> The record won Best International Artist for the group at the Toronto Independent Music Awards<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| coauthors =| title =Toronto Independent Music Awards Winners| page =| publisher =| date =| url =http://torontoima.com/new/awards/| accessdate =20 April 2011}}</ref> and a Single of the Year at the LA Music Awards.<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| coauthors =| title =LA Music Awards| page =| publisher =| date =| url =http://www.lamusicawards.com| accessdate =}}</ref> The band was one of 15 rock music finalists in the International Songwriting Competition (nominated alongside fellow Australians, [[Eskimo Joe]]).<ref>{{cite news| title =ISC Winners 08| url =http://www.songwritingcompetition.com/winners.htm| url-status =dead| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20100807225624/http://www.songwritingcompetition.com/Winners.htm| archivedate =7 August 2010| df =dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 the Sunpilots toured Australia twice more for their March of the Drones and Animals in My Mind tours. During the second tour the band performed at the One Movement Festival in Perth with the Hilltop Hoods, Sarah Blasko, Little Red and Kate Miller-Heidke<ref>{{cite news| last =| first =| title =One Movement for Music Announce Winners| page =| publisher =| date =16 October 2009| url =http://www.hotsource.com.au/news/1232/One_Movement_For_Music_Announce_Winners| accessdate =}}</ref> and were MySpace Featured Artists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soundsaustralia.com.au/downloads/midem2011_soundsaustralia.pdf|title=Sounds Australia \u2013 MIDEM 2011 booklet|website=Sounds Australia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409231246/http://www.soundsaustralia.com.au/downloads/MIDEM2011_SoundsAustralia.pdf|archive-date=2013-04-09|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' and move to Berlin (2010\u201315) ==\n\nIn 2010 the Sunpilots began working on their second album, ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues''. Following the completion of tracking at [[Studios 301]] in September, the band relocated to Berlin to tour Europe extensively.<ref>{{Citation|last=The Sunpilots|title=We Are The Sunpilots (Ep 1): Australian Nomads|date=2012-04-07|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNSkyTWJRkE|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref> They performed their first European show at the Popkomm Festival at Berlin Music Week 2010 on 9 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.messe-berlin.de/vip8_1/website/Internet/Internet/www.popkomm/deutsch/Popkomm-Showcase-Festival/Line-Up/index.jsp|title=Popkomm Showcase Festival blog|last=|first=|publisher=Popkomm|accessdate=}}</ref> ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' was mixed in Berlin by German engineer [[:de:Peter Schmidt (Tonmeister)|Peter Schmidt]] in late 2011 and released worldwide in 2012. The record is a dystopian [[concept album]] about \"human need for security and the freedoms we are willing to trade in return\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rockfreaks.net/albums/5139|title=The Sunpilots \u2013 ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' \u2013 Album Review | first = Petteri | last = Pertola | work = Rockfreaks.net | accessdate = 28 October 2017 }}</ref>\n\nThe Sunpilots toured Europe from 2011 to 2015, performing over 400 shows at festivals and clubs in the UK, Germany, Austria, Switzerland, France, Sweden, Netherlands, Belgium, Italy, Poland, Slovenia, Lithuania and Latvia. In September 2014 they completed their first US tour, performing 65 shows across 35 states.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thesunpilots.com/tourdates|title=The Sunpilots - Tour Dates (past shows)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110316014322/http://www.thesunpilots.com/tourdates|archive-date=2011-03-16|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nDuring this time the band also became known for staying with their fans on tour<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.muzikdizcovery.com/2013/03/album-review-sunpilots-king-of.html|title=Album Review: The Sunpilots - King of the Sugarcoated Tongues|website=www.muzikdizcovery.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> and performing in [[Mauerpark]] near the Berlin Wall.<ref>{{Citation|last=Thorsten Neuhetzki|title=Sunpilots im Mauerpark Berlin|date=2016-07-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xn8_lsh-QQI|accessdate=2017-05-16}}</ref>\n\n== Upcoming record (2016 - present) ==\n\nThe Sunpilots began work on their third album in early 2016 and have launched a crowdfunding campaign to fund it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pledge.thesunpilots.com|title=Pledge {{!}} The Sunpilots|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417194749/http://pledge.thesunpilots.com|archive-date=2016-04-17|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album, which is being recorded in Spain and Berlin, is slated for release in late 2017 and will be followed by an extensive world tour.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pledge.thesunpilots.com/new-album-and-world-tour/progress-and-release-date|title=New album progress and release date|work=Pledge {{!}} The Sunpilots|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-AU}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016 the band took a break from recording to tour Canada.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thesunpilots.com/news/our-first-canada-tour-kicks-off-this-week|title=Our first Canada tour kicks off this week|work=The Sunpilots|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-AU}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n\n=== Current line-up ===\n\n* Raj Siva-Rajah (2006\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 vocals\n* Bob Spencer (2006\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 guitar\n* Kay Ketting (2013\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Stefan Bielik (2015\u2013present)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n\n=== Previous members ===\n\n* Gavin Collison (2006)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n* Anthony Soole (2006\u201307)&nbsp;\u2013 percussion<ref name=\"MacLeod\"/>\n* Rob Ewan (2007)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar<ref name=\"Wilson\"/>\n* Justin Kool (2009\u201312)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n* Andrew Nielsen (2009\u201311)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Tom McGirr (2011\u201312)&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* Adil Baktir (2012\u201315)&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n\n* ''Living Receiver'' (2009)\n* ''King of the Sugarcoated Tongues'' (2012)\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n\n* ''The Sunpilots'' (self-titled 5-track EP) (2006)\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n* ''Spotlight in the Sun'' (2007)\n* ''You're Gonna Be a Star'' (2008)\n* ''Drones'' (2009)\n* ''Animals in My Mind'' (2009)\n* ''The Piper's Mirror'' (2012)\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{Official website|thesunpilots.com}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sunpilots, The}}\n[[Category:New South Wales musical groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2006]]\n[[Category:Australian post-grunge groups]]\n[[Category:Australian indie rock groups]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFormation and early days:replaced: moved to Sydney \u2192 moved to Sydney,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Sunpilots"}
{"title_page": "Metawin Opas-iamkajorn", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Thai actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Metawin Opas-iamkajorn\n| image              =\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| native_name        = \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e20\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e21\u0e02\u0e08\u0e23\n| native_name_lang   = tha\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1999|02|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| height             = {{height|ft=6|in=0.7}}\n| other_names        = Win\n| occupation         = [[Actor]]\n| years_active       = 2019\u2013present\n| notable_works      = {{plainlist|\n*Tine in ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]''\n}}\n| agent              = [[GMMTV]]\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Metawin Opas-iamkajorn''' ({{lang-th|\u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e20\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e21\u0e02\u0e08\u0e23}}; also known as '''Win''' ({{lang-th|\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19}}), born February 21, 1999) is a [[Thailand|Thai]] actor. He is known for his main role as ''Tine'' in [[GMMTV]]'s ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' (2020) where he stars as [[Vachirawit Chiva-aree]]'s love interest.<ref>{{cite web |title=Biodata Aktor Thailand Win Metawin Opa-iamkajorn |url=https://dianiopiari.com/biodata-aktor-thailand-win-metawin-opas-iamkajorn/ |website=dianiopiari.com |publisher=Diani Opiari |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Indonesian |date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e15\u0e35\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e41\u0e15\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e41\u0e23\u0e01 \u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e46 \u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e19\u0e14\u0e39\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e41\u0e2e\u0e0a\u0e41\u0e17\u0e47\u0e01 #\u0e17\u0e35\u0e21\u0e41\u0e21\u0e48\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.sanook.com/movie/96441/ |website=sanook.com |publisher=Sanook |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nMetawin was born in Bangkok, Thailand. He completed his secondary education in Panyarat High School where he had the opportunity to become an exchange student in [[Belmond-Klemme Community School District]] at [[Iowa]], [[United States]].<ref>{{cite web |title= #FantalkwithWin|url=https://twitter.com/winmetawin/status/1244628358228365315 |website=twitter.com |publisher=@winmetawin |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref> He became a member of the percussion choir in Belmond-Klemme High School band, where his group received a Superior rating.<ref>{{cite web |title= Musicians get lots of 'ones'|url=http://www.belmondnews.com/news/musicians-get-lots-of-ones/article_808c1cb8-b7a9-540d-802e-eb040d634a79.html|website=belmondnews.com |publisher= The Belmond Independent |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=English |date= 14 April 2016}}</ref> He also passed the [[General Educational Development]] (GED) examination upon his graudation. He is currently taking up Economics (International Program) in [[Thammasat University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e2b\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d \"\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\" \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.daradaily.com/news/89519/read |website=daradaily.com |publisher=Daradaily |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e19\u0e31\u0e01\u0e41\u0e2a\u0e14\u0e07\u0e14\u0e32\u0e27\u0e23\u0e38\u0e48\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e38\u0e48\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e07 185 \u0e0b\u0e21. \u0e08\u0e32\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e49\u0e27\u0e18\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e2d\u0e34\u0e19\u0e40\u0e15\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e4c |url=https://www.sanook.com/campus/1399827/ |website=sanook.com |publisher=Sanook |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMetawin made his acting debut with a main role as ''Tine'' in the ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' in 2019, a [[romance film|romantic]] [[comedy-drama]] [[television series]] produced by [[GMMTV]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e2b\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d \"\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\" \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.daradaily.com/news/89519/read |website=daradaily.com |publisher=Daradaily |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='2Gether': Here's everything to know about the Thai boy love show |url=https://filmdaily.co/news/2gether/|website=filmdaily.co |publisher=Film Daily |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=English}}</ref> He has also starred as a guest on several [[GMMTV]] shows such as [[School Rangers]] and [[Talk with Toey]]. He appeared as a surprise guest together with [[Vachirawit Chiva-aree]] in the [[YouTube]] channel of Thai comedian [[Watchara Sukchum]] (Jennie Panhan). <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e04 (\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 EP.9) \u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e07\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e01\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e39\u0e19\u0e30 [ENG SUB] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aW9S4PSDGeY|website=youtube.com |publisher=Jennie Panhan |accessdate=22 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn his Twitter interaction with fans, he revealed that his favorite soccer player is [[FC Barcelona|Futbol Club Barcelona]]'s forward, [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite web |title= #FantalkwithWin|url=https://twitter.com/winmetawin/status/1244627082744713216 |website=twitter.com |publisher=@winmetawin |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2020\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | [[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]\n| Tine\n| Main Role\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=#\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 2gether The Series\" \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e41\u0e2a \u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e25\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 EP1 \u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\u0e39 \u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 #\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e23\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e23 #\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e04 |url=https://medhubnews.com/\u0e14\u0e39\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21-64752-\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39-\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19-2gether-the-series-\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e01.html |website=medhubnews.com |publisher=Med Hub News |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | [[School Rangers]]\n| Himself\n| Guest\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e23\u0e16\u0e42\u0e23\u0e07\u0e40\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e19 School Rangers [EP.112] \u0e23\u0e23.\u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e2d\u0e38\u0e14\u0e21\u0e28\u0e36\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e12\u0e19\u0e32\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23 \u0e15\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x8736B5bkc8 |website=youtube.com |publisher=GMMTV |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | [[Talk with Toey]]\n| Himself\n| Guest\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e17\u0e2d\u0e25\u0e4c\u0e01-\u0e01\u0e30-\u0e40\u0e17\u0e22 EP.13 \u0e41\u0e02\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e40\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e0d '\u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17 \u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c, \u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19, \u0e41\u0e1e\u0e19\u0e40\u0e04\u0e49\u0e01 \u0e40\u0e02\u0e21\u0e19\u0e34\u0e08'| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=81vxGZJGV54|website=youtube.com |publisher=GMMTV |accessdate= 14 April 2020 |language=Thai |date= 5 April 2020 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Music Video Appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Artist\n! Role\n! Notes\n! {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2020\n| ''Tit Gub (\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e01\u0e31\u0e1a)'' || [[Natthawut Jenmana]] (Max) || Tine || ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' opening theme || <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e01\u0e31\u0e1a Ost.\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 2gether The Series - \u0e41\u0e21\u0e47\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e4c \u0e40\u0e08\u0e19\u0e21\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQaI3VkSCi0 |website=youtube.com |publisher=GMMTV Records |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Kan Goo (\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39)'' || [[Vachirawit Chiva-aree]] (Bright) || Tine || ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' ending theme || <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 Ost.\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 2gether The Series - \u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17 \u0e27\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e23\u0e27\u0e34\u0e0a\u0e0d\u0e4c |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=leevExpA8ec |website=youtube.com |publisher=GMMTV Records |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter|winmetawin}}\n* {{Instagram|winmetawin}}\n* {{Weibo | id= 7412472630 | name= Metawin Opas-iamkajorn }}\n* {{IMDb name | nm11456309 | Metawin Opas-Iamkajorn }}\n\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Thai male models]]\n[[Category:21st-century Thai male actors]]\n[[Category:Thai people of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Thai male actors]]\n[[Category:Thai male television actors]]\n[[Category:People from Bangkok]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Thai actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Metawin Opas-iamkajorn\n| image              =\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| native_name        = \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e20\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e21\u0e02\u0e08\u0e23\n| native_name_lang   = tha\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1999|02|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| alma_mater         = \n| height             = {{height|ft=6|in=0.7}}\n| other_names        = Win\n| occupation         = [[Actor]]\n| years_active       = 2019\u2013present\n| notable_works      = {{plainlist|\n*Tine in ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]''\n}}\n| agent              = [[GMMTV]]\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Metawin Opas-iamkajorn''' ({{lang-th|\u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e20\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e21\u0e02\u0e08\u0e23}}; also known as '''Win''' ({{lang-th|\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19}}), born February 21, 1999) is a [[Thailand|Thai]] actor. He is known for his main role as ''Tine'' in [[GMMTV]]'s ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' (2020) where he stars as [[Vachirawit Chiva-aree]]'s love interest.<ref>{{cite web |title=Biodata Aktor Thailand Win Metawin Opa-iamkajorn |url=https://dianiopiari.com/biodata-aktor-thailand-win-metawin-opas-iamkajorn/ |website=dianiopiari.com |publisher=Diani Opiari |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Indonesian |date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e15\u0e35\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e41\u0e15\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e41\u0e23\u0e01 \u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e46 \u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e19\u0e14\u0e39\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e41\u0e2e\u0e0a\u0e41\u0e17\u0e47\u0e01 #\u0e17\u0e35\u0e21\u0e41\u0e21\u0e48\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.sanook.com/movie/96441/ |website=sanook.com |publisher=Sanook |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nMetawin was born in Bangkok, Thailand. He completed his secondary education in Panyarat High School where he had the opportunity to become an exchange student in [[Belmond-Klemme Community School District]] at [[Iowa]], [[United States]].<ref>{{cite web |title= #FantalkwithWin|url=https://twitter.com/winmetawin/status/1244628358228365315 |website=twitter.com |publisher=@winmetawin |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref> He became a member of the percussion choir in Belmond-Klemme High School band, where his group received a Superior rating.<ref>{{cite web |title= Musicians get lots of 'ones'|url=http://www.belmondnews.com/news/musicians-get-lots-of-ones/article_808c1cb8-b7a9-540d-802e-eb040d634a79.html|website=belmondnews.com |publisher= The Belmond Independent |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=English |date= 14 April 2016}}</ref> He also passed the [[General Educational Development]] (GED) examination upon his graudation. He is currently taking up Economics (International Program) in [[Thammasat University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e2b\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d \"\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\" \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.daradaily.com/news/89519/read |website=daradaily.com |publisher=Daradaily |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e19\u0e31\u0e01\u0e41\u0e2a\u0e14\u0e07\u0e14\u0e32\u0e27\u0e23\u0e38\u0e48\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e38\u0e48\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e07 185 \u0e0b\u0e21. \u0e08\u0e32\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e49\u0e27\u0e18\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e2d\u0e34\u0e19\u0e40\u0e15\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e4c |url=https://www.sanook.com/campus/1399827/ |website=sanook.com |publisher=Sanook |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMetawin made his acting debut with a main role as ''Tine'' in the ''[[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]'' in 2019, a [[romance film|romantic]] [[comedy-drama]] [[television series]] produced by [[GMMTV]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \"\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e21\u0e18\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e2b\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d \"\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\" \u0e43\u0e19 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19\" |url=https://www.daradaily.com/news/89519/read |website=daradaily.com |publisher=Daradaily |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='2Gether': Here's everything to know about the Thai boy love show |url=https://filmdaily.co/news/2gether/|website=filmdaily.co |publisher=Film Daily |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=English}}</ref> He has also starred as a guest on several [[GMMTV]] shows such as [[School Rangers]] and [[Talk with Toey]]. He appeared as a surprise guest together with [[Vachirawit Chiva-aree]] in the [[YouTube]] channel of Thai comedian [[Watchara Sukchum]] (Jennie Panhan). <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e23\u0e35\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e04 (\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 EP.9) | \u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e07\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e01\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e39\u0e19\u0e30 [ENG SUB] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aW9S4PSDGeY|website=youtube.com |publisher=Jennie Panhan |accessdate=22 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn his Twitter interaction with fans, he revealed that his favorite soccer player is [[FC Barcelona|Futbol Club Barcelona]]'s forward, [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite web |title= #FantalkwithWin|url=https://twitter.com/winmetawin/status/1244627082744713216 |website=twitter.com |publisher=@winmetawin |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2020\n| style=\"font-style:italic;\" | [[2gether: The Series (Thai TV series)|2gether: The Series]]\n| Tine\n| Main Role\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=#\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 \"\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 2gether The Series\" \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e41\u0e2a \u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e41\u0e15\u0e48\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e25\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39 EP1 \u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\u0e39 \u0e44\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e27\u0e34\u0e19 #\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e23\u0e27\u0e31\u0e15\u0e23 #\u0e44\u0e17\u0e19\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e04 |url=https://medhubnews.com/\u0e14\u0e39\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21-64752-\u0e04\u0e31\u0e48\u0e19\u0e01\u0e39-\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e32\u0e30\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e04\u0e39\u0e48\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19-2gether-t